The paper deals with probabilistic graphical models and their conversion, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of sum-product networks (SPNs) and Bayesian networks (BNs) also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves algorithms and computational methods for inference, which could be categorized under data structures (cs.DS). The use of graphical models also suggests a potential connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) or computer vision (cs.CV), although these are less likely than the previous categories.
